<div class="style-guide-section">
  <h3>Production Helper Demo</h3>
  <p>Testing the new <code>habit_checkbox</code> helper with clean composable partials:</p>
  
  <div class="checkbox-variations">
    <h4>Basic Usage Examples</h4>
    
    <div class="checkbox-grid">
      <div class="checkbox-item">
        <%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 0) %>
        <span class="checkbox-label">Empty Box 0</span>
      </div>
      
      <div class="checkbox-item">
        <%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 3, fill_variant: 5, fill_style: :blot) %>
        <span class="checkbox-label">Box 3 + Blotch 5</span>
      </div>
      
      <div class="checkbox-item">
        <%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 7, fill_variant: 2, fill_style: :x) %>
        <span class="checkbox-label">Box 7 + X 2</span>
      </div>
      
      <div class="checkbox-item">
        <%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 9, fill_variant: 8, fill_style: :blot) %>
        <span class="checkbox-label">Box 9 + Blotch 8</span>
      </div>
      
      <div class="checkbox-item">
        <%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 1, fill_variant: 9, fill_style: :x) %>
        <span class="checkbox-label">Box 1 + X 9</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="usage-example" style="background: var(--paper-light); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 30px;">
    <h4>API Usage:</h4>
    <pre><code>&lt;%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 3, fill_variant: 5, fill_style: :blot) %&gt;</code></pre>
    <pre><code>&lt;%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 7, fill_variant: 2, fill_style: :x) %&gt;</code></pre>
    <pre><code>&lt;%= habit_checkbox(box_variant: 0) %&gt;</code></pre>
    
    <h4>Benefits:</h4>
    <ul style="margin-top: 15px; color: var(--ink-primary); opacity: 0.8;">
      <li>✅ <strong>Fast rendering</strong> - No Ruby hash processing</li>
      <li>✅ <strong>Rails caching works</strong> - Individual partials cached</li>
      <li>✅ <strong>Complete flexibility</strong> - Any box with any fill</li>
      <li>✅ <strong>Clean API</strong> - Clear, semantic parameters</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>